headline: Dover (DOV) Margin Decline Challenges Bullish Narratives Despite Valuation Signals
summary: Dover (DOV) posted net profit margins of 13.4%, trailing last year’s 18.4%, with earnings showing a negative trend over the past twelve months. Despite this recent softness, the company’s five-year average annual earnings growth stands at 8.5%, and forecasts call for 12.1% earnings growth per year on 5% annual revenue gains. This pace lags the broader US market. See our full analysis for Dover. Next, we will see how these latest numbers compare to the broader narratives shaping sentiment...

headline: DOV Q3 Deep Dive: Margin Expansion and Productivity Offset Organic Revenue Headwinds
summary: Manufacturing company Dover (NYSE:DOV) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025 as sales rose 4.8% year on year to $2.08 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.62 per share was 4.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock to Own for Decades and 2 We Question
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.
